After several days, I've come to the conclusion that TW thought we wiped. (Arguably we did, although I don't personally consider ~10 deaths and a camp-out a wipe. We were back up and running at 100% capacity within 10 mins)<br>
<br>
TW decided to take the opportunity to take a shot at the encounter, since they thought we wiped. However, TW took ~15 mins between the time they checked /who and thought we wiped, and the moment they actually ported up. Checking again even 5 mins after the first check would have shown our full raid force back in zone. Communication between the guilds would have helped, of course, but as my officers pointed out, Prien was aware of our situation, but Hurtt overrode him.<br>
<br>
So, TW ported up, saw us fully engaged in the encounter. (I'm still unsure where the whole &quot;FE was kiting the mob while rezzing 80% of their raid&quot; description came from, it was completely untrue.) So, TW was in the room, frustrated and couldn't easily leave without evaccing/gating. They were still hoping we'd wipe and they'd get a shot.<br>
<br>
Due to the animosity between our guilds, several misunderstandings were perpetuated. TW members were (IMO mostly unintentionally) interfering with our kill. Several members were running all over the room, observing the different aspects of the fight. And honestly, when Emp spawns, there are quite a few things that even TW's presence could easily have messed up. <br>
<br>
Emp encounter seriously has a 12+ major aspects that need to be dealt with simultaneously and successfully for a victory. There are MANY ways to lose that fight, even if you've done it multiple times and your entire guild knows what to expect. So a rival guild's presence in the room had a lot of potential to ruin the encounter for us... not to mention that many members don't get along hehe<br>
<br>
IMO, I have no problem understanding why TW ported up in the first place, it was a misunderstanding. I'm not sure why it took you ~15 mins to actually port up though. But after TW realized we were fully engaged in the encounter, they should have either left immediately or kept tight control on the entire guild. Kept EVERYONE in the entrance hall. Don't allow anyone to talk in public channels, cast AE buffs, wander around the room, etc.. Any of these things only add to what most FE assume... either you were there to purposely mess us up or to get a first-hand view of how to successfully handle the encounter.<br>
<br>
Don't give us any reasons to doubt your intentions and things will go over much smoother in future run-ins. I think most of us accept the fact that a guild loses it's shot at a mob if it wipes. If another guild steps in immediately after the mob has reset, it's no harm, no foul, in my opinion. <br>
<br>
That said... in all honesty, there are only two times you could &quot;take over&quot; Emp encounter... before Blood dies or after. Before he dies, all you would have to do is let him reset, then start him from scratch. But after Blood dies, if we wiped on Emp himself... trust me, it IS impossible to take over, even if you had beat him before and knew exactly what it takes to beat him. He's the hardest mob in the game and he comes with a posse too. =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/ukalran.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalran</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>QHills and Clueless</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#628CBC>(9/30/02 1:18:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=534>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Leeches</span><hr size=1> I wholeheartedly agree that better communication between the guilds is essential.  However, there has to be some mutual respect and just pure honesty.  From what I understand, you guys were perfectly aware of what was happening, and Hurtt decided to take it into his own hands to port up.<br>
